cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper discusses a defense mechanism for deep learning models against adversarial attacks, which is a common topic in the sub-fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves heuristic attacks and evaluating the robustness of the defense mechanism, which are relevant to the sub-fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the use of k-Nearest Neighbor algorithm and deep learning suggests a connection to the sub-field of neural networks (cs.NE).
